*Retirement (4)
*Retirement is a silly word. None of my friends who have been retired by 
their employers have retired from being active in some way. I see 
retirement as an exchange of the constraints imposed by some employer 
for the constraints imposed by age - and perhaps one's spouse. I am not 
sure whether this is a desirable bargain but what the heck, that is what 
happens and we all have to make the best of it. Cheers, Rolf
