*Conference on "ICT for Rural Economic Development"
*18-19 November 2010 (in BERLIN & online) - invitation to participate
Eighty high level experts will meet in Berlin to explore the potential 
of Information and Communication Technologies (ICT) for economic 
development in rural areas of developing countries. Organized by GTZ on 
behalf of the Federal Ministry for Economic Cooperation and Development 
(BMZ), the conference participants will debate e-agriculture, ICT 
business innovation, ICT-backed financial service development, and 
universal access to ICT infrastructures.

They will share project practice and experiences, analyse the impact of 
ICT policies and regulations, the benefits of ICT for local communities, 
and investigate innovative business models as well as the impact of new 
technologies. To review the full list of topics and discussion groups, 
you can access the agenda at http://ict.ez-blogs.de/.

You are invited to virtually follow the discussion online during the 
conference, through GTZ's ICT4D Blog: http://ict.ez-blogs.de/and Twitter 
using the #ICTGTZ tag. If you wish to comment on the posted summaries, 
you can register on the blog page. Registration is open to all.

The following organizations will participating in the conference: FAO, 
UNCTAD, InfoDev, CTO, BMZ, BMELV, BMWi, Ministry of Foreign Affairs of 
Finland, DFID, GTZ, DED, KfW, InWent, Tufts University, , Fraunhofer, 
University of Siegen, Royal Holloway, IICD, Kabissa, LinkNet Zambia, 
Kiwanja.net, GSMA, BITKOM, SAP, NSN, Manobi, MicroBanker, Detecon, 
Intelecon, BIID, etc.

The debate will continue online after the conference hosted on the 
e-Agriculture Community at http://www.e-agriculture.org/ from 24 
November to 1 December 2010. All e-Agriculture Community members are 
invited to participate. You can join e-Agriculture by registering free 
online.

See: http://www.e-agriculture.org/forums/discussions/gtz-discussion
See: http://www.gtz.de/en
See: http://www.bmz.de/en


